  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="2"/>
   <head>The Bookes verdict.</head>
   <l>With hart receiue, with mind embrase:</l>
   <l>This small woorke, though name be base.</l>
   <l>The Reader may, with carefull paine,</l>
   <l>By perusing it, some profite gaine.</l>
   <l>Refuse not thou, which is thine owne,</l>
   <l>Thou reapest that, thou hast not sowne.</l>
   <l>The Author holdes it, double gaine,</l>
   <l>Jf thou with patience, peruse the same.</l>
   <l>Content therin, his willing mind,</l>
   <l>So shall you reape, that is behind.</l>
   <closer>Farewell.</closer>
</div>
